Let X be a non-singular algebraic variety of dimension n, and let Y be an algebraic subset of dimension q=n-p of X. Let \mathscr { F } be a coherent algebraic sheaf on X with support contained in Y, and let \mathscr { L } be a locally-free algebraic sheaf on X. Then the sheaves \mathscr {E} \kern -1.5pt \mathit {xt} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}^i( \mathscr { F } , \mathscr { L } ) are zero for i<p, and, when i=p, there is a canonical isomorphism
